Powers of 2
A powers of ten video for physical toys.  A powers of 2 toy would work as a
toy in its regular state, but you could peel away layers of the toy
revealing its inner workings at a more detailed level.  the ultimate powers
of 2 toy would let you put any object in a powers of 2 box and then "see"
into that object at progressively higher levels of functional magnification.

Lightbright meets bread board
A lightbright toy that enables you to wire logic in addition to creating
static patterns.  you could store a series of states, create dynamic
patterns, "program" interactions among lights, explore emergent patterns,
and so on.  

Really magic 8 ball
listens to your questions and reconfigures meaningful answers



